-- Turkey's Petkim agrees to sell 30 pct of Petlim port to Goldman for $250 mln
-- By Daren Butler
-- Fri Dec 19, 2014 09:14AM EST
-- None



ISTANBUL, Dec 19 (Reuters) - Turkish petrochemicals company Petkim <PETKM.IS> said on Friday it had agreed to sell a 30 percent stake in its Petlim port to Goldman Sachs <GS.N> for $250 million.

Talks for the sale had started in February this year. Petkim and Petlim are controlled by the Turkish branch of Azeri energy group Socar. [ID:nL6N0PW1JX]